.SH NAME
\fBhscan\fP \- scan along the \fBH\fP\-axis in reciprocal space
.\" spec reStructuredText documentation
.
\fP
.PP
.\" @(#)hscan.rst        6.1  08/01/12  CSS
.
.\" Copyright (c) 1990,1991,1995,2012 Certified Scientific Software
.
.\" 
.
.\" versioninfo: "hscan" "macro" "08/01/12" "hscan.rst 6.1  08/01/12 CSS"
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.rs
.sp
\fBhscan start end intervals time\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.rs
.sp
\fBhscan\fP is a linear scan in reciprocal space along the
\fBH\fP\-axis from \fBstart\fP to \fBend\fP. The step size is
\fB(start\-end)/intervals\fP.
The number of data points collected will be \fBintervals+1\fP.
Count time is given by \fBtime\fP, which if positive,
specifies seconds and if negative, specifies monitor counts.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.rs
.sp
\fBhscan .9 1.1 10 10\fP
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.rs
.sp
